user_specs: ['Eye Color Green', 'Hair color Black', 'Skin Tone Fair', 'Skin Type Dry']
review_content: I love this blush and the natural flush it gives me. I feel like you can barely tell I have blush on and I love that about it. I have fair skin with freckles and dark; almost black hair. This is a gorgeous peachy shade that looks very natural. I love it and I think it’s my new daily blush!

user_specs: ['Eye Color Blue', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Porcelain', 'Skin Type Normal']
review_content: I am super pale, like legit white. When swatching on my hand, the shade is very light peach and pretty. However, I cannot for the life of me get it to stay on my face! I tried different brushes, but it won't work. 1-star for transparent "blush"

user_specs: ['Age over 54', 'Eye Color Blue', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Fair', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content: I would describe this as a glowy, sheer, pastel peach blush. As someone with pale skin that's nearly translucent, this is a lovely peach option that doesnt pull too orange. However, I can definitely see how this wouldn't really show up on darker skintones. It smells sweet and I'm looking forward to using this for spring and summer!

user_specs: ['Eye Color Hazel', 'Hair color Red', 'Skin Tone Light', 'Skin Type Oily']
review_content: There’s nothing there.. If I swatch it 3 times on my hand I can get pigment but on a brush.. there’s nothing. I really wanted to like this since I’m from Georgia and peach is my favorite color but for $30 I don’t think so. Will be returning it.

user_specs: ['Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Fair', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content: If you were expecting old Georgia, it’s not, there’s sparkle now. Swatching it I didn’t like it much. But once I used it on my face, it was very beautiful! I used a little Dandelion first and then laid Georgia on top. Please can we have OG georgia back!!
